description:
Today for those who visit Israel, many stop on the Mount of Olives through popular tourism groups. The view of Jerusalem is stunning with the site of the old Jewish Temple in the foreground. Here Jesus stood and looked down across over the city and gave his disciples a warning of the destruction of Jerusalem and the end of the world. The signs were similar for both events, even though they are separated by 2000 years of world history, with the warning for us today being particularly apt - 'Take heed that no man deceive you'.
